# SDK Governance (Autoconnecto Arduino/ESP32)

The `sdk/` project is an Arduino library implementing device transport and parity features.

Confirmed patterns:
- MQTT-over-WSS broker URI (`wss://{host}:{wssPort}/mqtt`)
- Device-scoped topics for telemetry and attributes
- Global singleton event dispatch pointer inside `MQTTTransport.cpp`

## Transport contract discipline

- MQTT topic names are a compatibility contract with the backend.
- Any change to topics/payloads must be coordinated with backend consumers and documented in:
  - `sdk/TRANSPORT_ARCHITECTURE.md`
  - `backend/ARCHITECTURE.md`
  - root `ARCHITECTURE.md`

## Single-instance constraint (confirmed)

- `MQTTTransport.cpp` uses a global pointer to route static callbacks.
- Do not introduce designs requiring multiple concurrent transport instances unless this constraint is intentionally removed and documented.

## Deterministic device behavior

- Avoid blocking loops unless explicitly required (WiFi connect currently blocks; any change must consider device UX and watchdog).
- Reconnect logic must be explicit and bounded (backoff, retry cadence).
- Maintain idempotent behavior where feasible (MQTT can redeliver).

## Rollback-first firmware compatibility

- Assume field devices upgrade slowly; avoid breaking topic/payload changes without dual-compat windows.
- When changing transport behavior, provide:
  - compatibility notes
  - expected broker requirements
  - downgrade path (old firmware behavior still supported or explicitly sunset)

